}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11921/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11921/canvas/1/ecfb534e-a58e-44d6-b4ef-af6743f87da5","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:57:48.815Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As Cyril enters the room, she walks by Alma’s shoes that she removed when she sat beside Reynolds. Cyril keeps hers on, the clacking of her heels interrupting <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW82690107 BCX2\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-11947.html\"><u>the silence he longs for</u></a>. Alma has removed her shoes, making her footsteps quieter and making herself at home in his room, while Cyril now is the interloper in his space.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11921/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:611.7803660565723,224.5257903494176,462.4292845257903,831.4143094841932"}}}]}]}]}